<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870220-0097 </DOCNO><HL> Control Data Gets Sony Order</HL><DD> 02/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CDA SNE </IN><DATELINE> MINNEAPOLIS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Control Data Corp. said it received a three-year contract from Sony Corp. of Japan for the purchase of Wren disk drives valued at about $80 million.    The computer concern said the Japanese electronics company is incorporating the 101-megabyte and 182-megabyte Wren III half-height and full-height disk drives in its NEWS 32-bit general purpose office and engineering microcomputer workstation systems. </TEXT></DOC>